title: VirtualBox 5.0.10 + Extension Pack Final All OS Nov2015 Seven7i
description:
Seven7i Presents

VirtualBox 5.0.10 Final All OS

(Released: Nov 11, 2015)

VirtualBoxVirtualBox: 
is an application installed on an existing 
host operating system; within this application, 
additional operating systems can be loaded and run, 
each with its own virtual environment. For example, 
several Linux distributions can be hosted on a single 
machine running Windows XP; likewise, XP and Vista 
can run on a machine running Linux, and so on. 
There is a free for personal or evaluation use 
proprietary version and a GNU General Public License (GPL) version.

Features:
Modularity
Virtual machine descriptions in XML
Guest Additions for Windows and Linux
Shared folders
Virtual USB Controllers
Remote Desktop Protocol
USB over RDP
